owdery who was leaving the church asserted josephs involvement  compton  p  counting at least  total wives smith  p  counting  wives brodie  pp – counting  wives bushman  pp   accepting comptons count excepting one wife quinn  pp – counting  wives remini  p  noting that the exact figure is still debated  foster  quinn  compton  bushman  pp – van wagoner  newell  avery  hales  hales discusses the historical records and context of  such sealings indicate they were eternityonly unions quinn  p  quinn acknowledged in  that a recently discovered historical record regarding ruth sayers indicates that the union applied only to the eternities after mortal life disproving his previouslyheld decadeslong assumption that excluded eternityonly sealings  compton  p  remini  p  brodie  pp – bushman  pp – smiths last marriage was in november  to fanny murray a fiftysixyearold widow his youngest plural wife helen mar kimball was fourteen  bushman  p  roberts  pp   bushman  p  noting smiths statements that unless he started to marry plural wives an angel would slay him brodie  p  the  revelation threatened destruction to any wife who refused to accept the new law  bushman  pp –  bushman  p   brodie  p  bushman  p  remini  pp –  hill  p  by assuring emma that her salvation would be virtually certain and all but the unpardonable sin would be merely visited with judgment in the flesh the revelation placed enormous pressure on emma to accept plural marriage bushman  pp – brodie  pp – revelation indicated emma would be destroyed if she refused polygamy  bushman  pp – saying that emmas participation in the endowment ceremonies may have contributed to softening her stance on plural marriage quinn  p  emma participated with smith in the later sealing ceremony bushman  p  sealed on may    bushman  p   bushman  p   bushman  p   roberts  pp    harris  p  saying that smith went through a threefold change of position on slavery initially opposing it in the s then supporting it with an strong antiabolitionist position in the mids then opposing it again in the early s  bushman  pp  – hill  pp – brodie  pp   hill  p   bushman  p  hill  pp –  bushman  p  hill  p   brodie  pp – bushman  p  bloom  p   bushman  pp –  see the thirteenth article of faith  roberts  p  bushman  p   quinn  p  quoting a letter smith wrote to nancy rigdon after she had rejected his proposal of polygamous marriage ostling  ostling  p   quinn  p   quinn  pp – referencesedit abanes richard  one nation under gods a history of the mormon church thunders mouth press isbn   allen james b autumn  the significance of joseph smiths first vision in mormon thought pdf dialogue a journal of mormon thought   –  avery vt newell lk  the lion and the lady brigham young and emma smith utah historical quarterly   –  bergera gary james ed  line upon line essays on mormon doctrine salt lake city signature books isbn   bloom harold  the american religion the emergence of the postchristian nation st ed new york simon  schuster isbn   brodie fawn m  no man knows my history the life of joseph smith nd ed new york alfred a knopf isbn   brooke john l  the refiners fire the making of mormon cosmology – cambridge cambridge university press isbn   bushman richard lyman  joseph smith rough stone rolling new york alfred a knopf isbn   bushman richard lyman  mormonism a very short introduction new york oxford university press isbn   compton todd  in sacred loneliness the plural wives of joseph smith salt lake city signature books isbn x  foster lawrence  religion and sexuality the shakers the mormons and the oneida community new york oxford university press isbn   hales brian  joseph smith’s sexual polyandry and the emperor’s new clothes on closer inspection what do we find sandy utah fairmormon formally foundation for apologetic information  research  harris martin  mormonism—no ii tiffanys monthly   –  harris matthew l bringhurst newell g  the mormon church and blacks a documentary history isbn   hill donna  joseph sm