ery who was leaving the church asserted josephs involvement  compton  p  counting at least  total wives smith  p  counting  wives brodie  pp – counting  wives bushman  pp   accepting comptons count excepting one wife quinn  pp – counting  wives remini  p  noting that the exact figure is still debated  foster  quinn  compton  bushman  pp – van wagoner  newell  avery  hales  hales discusses the historical records and context of  such sealings indicate they were eternityonly unions quinn  p  quinn acknowledged in  that a recently discovered historical record regarding ruth sayers indicates that the union applied only to the eternities after mortal life disproving his previouslyheld decadeslong assumption that excluded eternityonly sealings  compton  p  remini  p  brodie  pp – bushman  pp – smiths last marriage was in november  to fanny murray a fiftysixyearold widow his youngest plural wife helen mar kimball was fourteen  bushman  p  roberts  pp   bushman  p  noting smiths statements that unless he started to marry plural wives an angel would slay him brodie  p  the  revelation threatened destruction to any wife who refused to accept the new law  bushman  pp –  bushman  p   brodie  p  bushman  p  remini  pp –  hill  p  by assuring emma that her salvation would be virtually certain and all but the unpardonable sin would be merely visited with judgment in the flesh the revelation placed enormous pressure on emma to accept plural marriage bushman  pp – brodie  pp – revelation indicated emma would be destroyed if she refused polygamy  bushman  pp – saying that emmas participation in the endowment ceremonies may have contributed to softening her stance on plural marriage quinn  p  emma participated with smith in the later sealing ceremony bushman  p  sealed on may    bushman  p   bushman  p   bushman  p   roberts  pp    harris  p  saying that smith went through a threefold change of position on slavery initially opposing it in the s then supporting it with an strong antiabo