 them so they stood so far as i have witnessed  bushman  p   quinn  pp –  –     –  –   brodie  p  smith began to efface the communistic rubric of his young theology  brodie  pp – dc    brodie  pp – dc    bushman  pp – dc    bushman  pp – dc    brodie  p  bushman  pp – dc    brodie  p  bushman  p  joseph drank tea and a glass of wine from time to time ostling  ostling  pp – smith himself liked a nip every now and then especially at weddings the mansion house which operated a hotel maintained a fully stocked barroom and nauvoo also had a brewery  bushman  pp – dc    brodie  p  bushman  pp – dc    bushman  pp –  brodie  pp – bushman  pp –  bushman  p  joseph spoke like a witness or an initiate in heavenly mysteries rather than a prophet delivering revelations from the lords mouth  bushman  pp  – smiths first mention of baptism for the dead was in a funeral sermon in august  a letter on the subject is contained in dc    bushman  pp – arguing that smith may have been unaware of the other religious materialism arguments circulating in his day such as those of joseph priestley brooke  pp –smith  p  story from the book of ether of jesus revealing the body of my spirit to an especially faithful man saying humanity was created in the image of his spirit body  widmer  p   bushman  pp – bloom  p  smiths god is hedged in by limitations and badly needs intelligences besides his own  vogel dan the earliest mormon conception of god  in bergera  pp – arguing that smiths original view was modalism jesus being the embodied manifestation the spirit father and that by  smith shifted to a binitarian formulation favored by sidney rigdon which also viewed the father as a spirit alexander thomas the reconstruction of mormon doctrine from joseph smith to progressive theology  in bergera  p  prior to  smith viewed god the father as an absolute personage of spirit  widmer  p  alexander thomas the reconstruction of mormon doctrine from joseph smith to progressive theology  in bergera  p  describing smiths doctrine as material anthropomorphism bloom  p  smiths god after all began as a man and struggled heroically in and with time and space rather after the pattern of colonial and revolutionary americans  bushman  pp   joseph redefined the nature of god giving him a form and a body and locating him in time and space with a throne situated near a star or planet named kolob bloom  p  joseph smiths god  is finite  exalted now into the heavens god necessarily is still subject to the contingencies of time and space  vogel  p  roberts  p   larson  p  online ver widmer  p   widmer  p  bushman  pp    bushman  pp – –  bushman  p   bushman  p   brooke  p   remini  p   quinn  p  describing smiths earliest authority as charismatic authority  quinn  pp – bushman  pp   phelps  p  no one shall be appointed to receive commandments and revelations in this church excepting my servant joseph for he receiveth them even as moses  brodie  pp   –  quinn  pp –  describing the expected role of the council of fifty  quinn  pp – bushman  pp –  quinn  p   brodie  p bushman  pp – quinn  pp –roberts  pp – on june   the authority of the melchizedek priesthood was manifested and conferred for the first time upon several of the elders prince  pp  –   ostling  ostling  pp – prince  pp – –  bushman  p  that the nauvoo endowment is more akin to aspects of the kabbalah  prince  pp    brooke  pp  –   smith introduced the sealing power in  as part of the high priesthood and then attributed this power to elijah after he appeared in an  vision in the kirtland temple  brooke  pp  – brooke  pp   brooke  pp   bushman  pp – the second anointing ceremony was josephs attempt to deal with the theological problem of assurance of ones eternal life  roberts  pp –  revelation describing the new and everlasting covenant foster  pp –  foster  p   bushman  pp – those who were married eternally were then sealed by the holy spirit of promise through the second anointing brooke  pp –  roberts  pp – bushman  pp – b