 had become acquainted with the spirit of prophecy and revelation and no longer needed it  brodie  p   brodie  p  bushman  p   brodie  p  bushman  pp  xxi he experienced revelation like george fox the early quaker who heard the spirit as impersonal prophecy not from his own mind but as a word from the lord as the prophets and the apostles had bushman  p   bushman  p  noting that though smith declared the work finished in  the church lacked funds to publish it during his lifetime brodie  p  brodie suggests that rigdon may have prompted smith to revise the bible in response to an  revision by rigdons former mentor alexander campbell  bushman  p  smith said later in life i believe the bible as it ought to be as it came from the pen of the original writers  hill  p  although smith described his work beginning in april  as a translation he obviously meant a revision by inspiration  bushman  p   bushman  pp – in genesis enoch is summarized in five verses joseph smiths revision extends this to  verses  bushman  pp – joseph smiths book of moses fully christianized the old testament rather than hinting of the coming of christian truth the book of moses presents the whole gospel god teaches adam to believe repent and be baptized even by water  brodie  pp – bushman  pp  –  bushman  pp  –  john a wilson the joseph smith egyptian papyri translations and interpretations dialogue  summer   the papyri were prepared for the funerary rites of one tashertmin daughter of newkhensu  bushman  p   bushman  p  referring to smith dictating revelations pratt said each sentence was uttered slowly and very distinctly and with a pause between each sufficiently long for it to be recorded by an ordinary writer in long hand this was the manner in which all his revelations were dictated and written there was never any hesitation reviewing or reading back in order to keep the run of the subject neither did any of these communications undergo revisions interlinings or corrections as he dictated them 