miths doctrine as material anthropomorphism bloom  p  smiths god after all began as a man and struggled heroically in and with time and space rather after the pattern of colonial and revolutionary americans  bushman  pp   joseph redefined the nature of god giving him a form and a body and locating him in time and space with a throne situated near a star or planet named kolob bloom  p  joseph smiths god  is finite  exalted now into the heavens god necessarily is still subject to the contingencies of time and space  vogel  p  roberts  p   larson  p  online ver widmer  p   widmer  p  bushman  pp    bushman  pp – –  bushman  p   bushman  p   brooke  p   remini  p   quinn  p  describing smiths earliest authority as charismatic authority  quinn  pp – bushman  pp   phelps  p  no one shall be appointed to receive commandments and revelations in this church excepting my servant joseph for he receiveth them even as moses  brodie  pp   –  quinn  pp –  describing the expected role of the council of fifty  quinn  pp – bushman  pp –  quinn  p   brodie  p bushman  pp – quinn  pp –roberts  pp – on june   the authority of the melchizedek priesthood was manifested and conferred for the first time upon several of the elders prince  pp  –   ostling  ostling  pp – prince  pp – –  bushman  p  that the nauvoo endowment is more akin to aspects of the kabbalah  prince  pp    brooke  pp  –   smith introduced the sealing power in  as part of the high priesthood and then attributed this power to elijah after he appeared in an  vision in the kirtland temple  brooke  pp  – brooke  pp   brooke  pp   bushman  pp – the second anointing ceremony was josephs attempt to deal with the theological problem of assurance of ones eternal life  roberts  pp –  revelation describing the new and everlasting covenant foster  pp –  foster  p   bushman  pp – those who were married eternally were then sealed by the holy spirit of promise through the second anointing brooke  pp –  roberts  pp – bushman  pp – brooke  p   roberts  pp  i have appointed unto my servant joseph to hold this power in the last days and there is never but one on the earth at a time on whom this power and the keys of this priesthood are conferred  foster  pp – compton  pp  – smith  pp  brooke  p  brodie  p  bushman  p  noting that a modern mormon interpretation of smiths  polygamy revelation ties both polygamy and monogamy to degrees of exaltation  bloom  p  foster  p  if marriage with one wife  could bring eternal progression and ultimate godhood for men then multiple wives in this life and the next would accelerate the process in line with gods promise to abraham that his seed eventually would be as numerous as the sand on the sea shore brodie  p  if a man went to heaven with ten wives he would have more than tenfold the blessings of a mere monogamist for all the children begotten through these wives would enhance his kingdom  compton  p  bushman  pp   hill  p   gospel topics plural marriage in kirtland and nauvoo ldsorg lds church   bushman  pp – hill  p  noting that benjamin f johnson realized later that josephs polygamy was one cause of disruption and apostasy in kirtland although it was rarely discussed in public  probably between  and  bushman  p  noting that alger was fourteen in  when she met smith and her involvement with smith was between that date and  and that the relationship may have begun as early as  compton  p  bushman  p  noting comptons date and conclusion brodie  pp – bushman  pp – smith  pp – n cowdery questioned whether smith and alger were actually married and called it a dirty nasty filthy affair  bushman  pp – in  cowdery was charged with seeking to destroy the character of president joseph smith jr by falsely insinuating that he was guilty of adultry c fanny algers name was never mentioned but doubtless she was the women in question smith wanted it on record that he had never confessed to such a sin presumably he felt innocent because he had married alger only cowdery who was leaving the church asserted josephs involvement  compton  p  counting at least  total wives smith  p  counting  wives brodie  pp – counting  wives bushman  pp   accepting comptons count excepting one wife quinn  pp – counting  wives remini  p  noting that the exact figure is still debated  foster  quinn  compton  bushman  pp – van wagoner  newell  avery  hales  hales discusses the historical records and context of  such sealings indicate they were eternityonly unions quinn  p  quinn acknowledged in  that a recently discovered historical record regarding ruth sayers indicates that the union applied only to the eternities after mortal life disproving his previouslyheld decadeslong assumption that excluded eternityonly sealings  compton  p  remini  p  brodie  pp – bushman  pp – smiths last marriage was in november  to fanny murray a fiftysixyearold widow his youngest plural wife helen mar kimball was fourteen  bushman  p  roberts  pp   bushman  p  noting smiths statements that unless he started to marry plural wives an angel would slay him brodie  p  the  revelation threatened destruction to any wife who refused to accept the new law  bushman  pp –  bushman  p   brodie  p  bushman  p  remini  pp –  hill  p  by assuring emma that her salvation would be virtually certain and all but the unpardonable sin would be merely visited with judgment in the flesh the revelation placed enormous pressure on emma to accept plural marriage bushman  pp – brodie  pp – revelation indicated emma would be destroyed if she refused polygamy  bushman  pp – saying that emmas participation in the endowment ceremonies may have contributed to softening her stance on plural marriage quinn  p  emma participated with smith in the later sealing ceremony bushman  p  sealed on may    bushman  p   bushman  p   bushman  p   roberts  pp    harris  p  saying that smith went through a threefold change of position on slavery initially opposing it in the s then supporting it with an strong antiabolitionist po